comment_data.body:
I think you could just do

```
            ', '.join(tuple(arg.py_result() for arg in args) + ("NULL",))))
```

Not sure you need to allocate a temp. And it definitely doesn't need refcounting

commit.message:
Pad __pyx_callargs with NULL pointer

Closes gh-5668

This change resolve Coverity (a false-positive but annoying) issue
of reporting out-of-bound access to array __pyx_callargs in a call
to _Pyx_PyObject_FastCall.
Rewrite to avoid useless padding (and to let CI check if this is still enough).
